summary: “You know what’s really gonna blow your mind? One of my best friends growing up, one of the first people who got me interested...
caption: “You know what’s really gonna blow your mind? One of my best friends growing up, one of the first people who got me interested in film, he used to work at Northrop Aircraft Factory. His shift ended at 3:42. When we heard that, me and my other friends thought it was so ridiculous and we constantly made fun of it. And so 42, that number was all about my friend, Vincent, who has since passed on. In my mind, when I see it, it’s like a little angel bell ringing.” - Director Peter Ramsey 👼

blog.name: i-blame-my-love-of-whump-on-ryan
blog.title: I Enjoy Hurting Characters, Okay?
blog.description:
Do you enjoy Whump?

Then you’ll enjoy this page.

Probably.

I take writing prompts, so send ‘em in.

~ Follows from @bleusmainpage ~

body:
*No Title

Fandom : MCU

Characters : Peter Parker

Whump : Sick

* Pre-bite *

Peter got sick, a lot. He was used to it, at this point, but that didn’t mean he had to like it. The missing school, the saltines and tea, the stomach aches and migraines. It was too sick to come to school, but sick enough to the point where Peter felt like he had no real reason to stay home.

But there he was, laid out on the couch, not moving because of the terrible pain in his head, and freezing from the neck down under a pile of blankets. Nothing could be simple in his life, could it?

The television was turned on, and it was playing the news, something about Tony Stark and something new that he was doing that was probably going to be bad for people in the long run. Or, that’s what most people thought anyways. Peter thought that he was a hero, someone who was protecting the world. Sure, the guy knocked down a couple buildings, but who wouldn’t?

“I would,” Peter mumbled to himself, trying to force his attention on the screen when all he wanted to do was close his eyes. “He’s saving the world.”

The newscaster went on to talk about some other thing happening in some other country, which finally gave Peter the chance to let his focus drift, to let his heavy eye lids close.

I want to save the world, was his last thought as he drifted off.

[ @jackwriteswhump ]

summary: Konichiwa! It's Peni Parker! by HyperSpaceOddity  Into the Spider-verse is probably my new main fandom now. It’s like the Lego...
caption:
Konichiwa! It’s Peni Parker! by HyperSpaceOddity

Into the Spider-verse is probably my new main fandom now. It’s like the Lego Movie for an older audience. I honestly can’t say enough about it, but enough about my impending geek-out moment. This is one of my first major pieces of fanart for it.

Peni Parker is one of my favorites, but sometimes it bugs me how “american anime” she looks. I used this as an opportunity to see if I was still any good at anime, and I’m pretty happy with it!

summary: I JUST WATCHED INTO THE SPIDERVERSE!!!!!
question: I JUST WATCHED INTO THE SPIDERVERSE!!!!!
answer:
(Oops I just saw this I have no clue how old it is…)

That’s great my dude! And I can tell by your reaction that you loved it as much as many others do, myself included!

It is a visual masterpiece, and I consider it my second favorite animated film of all time (because nothing beats The Iron Giant)! I am so thrilled that it got the recognition it deserves, both at the box office and during awards season, and I can’t wait for the spin offs and sequels they have in the works!
